HEADWORD: Predecease
<hw>Pre`de*cease</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To die sooner
than.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧If children <xex>predecease</xex> progenitors.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predecease</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Predecease
<hw>Pre"de*cease`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The death of one
person or thing before another.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Brougham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predecessive</ent>⟦br⟧
